<br>
We have made several attempts at the fourth floor.  As I recall, someone's invis popped or the mummy that see's invis hits us, resulting in 5 - 8 mobs running through the halls to attack us as soon as we arrive on the other side of the mirror.  The enchanters mezzes AND stuns consistently get so heavily resisted as to make the enchanter unable to croud control. <br>
<br>
We are currently thinking of the following strategy:<br>
<br>
1. Go through mirror to the fourth floor. <br>
<br>
2. Enchanter stays invis while Warrior fights the stuff at entrance (with AOE assistance from the two druids) until all the stuff that aggroed on us is dead.  Cleric heals the warrior, Shaman heals the druids.  Keep fighting until all the aggroed mobs are dead.  Heal, buff and med up.<br>
<br>
3. Head through the fake wall and park the group there.  Pull any mobs that are between the group and the 5th floor mirror to the group, singly if possible.  When the way is clear, move the group to the mirror and exit to 5th floor (home sweet home :-)<br>
<br>
Do you think this strategy will work?  Or will it contribute yet another story to our guild name "Fiasco in Progress"?  :-)<br>
